      • ReminderRequestTimer

        public ReminderRequestTimer​(long countDownTimeInSeconds)
        A constructor used to create a ReminderRequestTimer instance. The countdown timer reminder will be triggered after a specified duration.

        Ensure that the input parameters meet the following requirements. Otherwise, the application may crash due to an illegal parameter exception.

        • The value of triggerTimeInSeconds must be greater than 0.
        Parameters:
        countDownTimeInSeconds - Indicates the duration after which this timer reminder will be triggered.
        Since:
        6

    • Method Detail

      • setTimeInterval

        public ReminderRequest setTimeInterval​(long timeIntervalInSeconds)
        Description copied from class: ReminderRequest
        Sets the snooze interval for this reminder, in seconds. The default value is 0.
        1. The minimum snooze interval is 5 minutes. If the snooze interval is set to a value greater than 0 and less than 5 minutes, the system converts it to 5 minutes by default.
        2. This method does not take effect on ReminderRequestTimer
Overrides:
setTimeInterval in class ReminderRequest
Parameters:
timeIntervalInSeconds - Indicates the snooze interval to set. If the value is less than or equal to 0, the reminder will not be snoozed.
Returns:
Returns this ReminderRequest instance.
